From: Masaharu Hayakawa <masaharu.hayakawa.ry@renesas.com>
Date: Tue, 21 Nov 2017 17:49:48 +0900
Subject: [PATCH 203/909] mmc: renesas_sdhi: Fix SCC error detection

commit 46c96a73da2f463809c3f2d5d147ea9a916ef25a from
git://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/horms/renesas-bsp.git

SDR104 and HS200 need to check SCC error.
When SCC error is detected, retuning is necessary.
In addition, SCC error checking during retuning is unnecessary.

Signed-off-by: Masaharu Hayakawa <masaharu.hayakawa.ry@renesas.com>
Signed-off-by: Takeshi Saito <takeshi.saito.xv@renesas.com>
Signed-off-by: Meng Li <Meng.Li@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/mmc/host/renesas_sdhi_core.c | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/mmc/host/renesas_sdhi_core.c b/drivers/mmc/host/renesas_sdhi_core.c
index f087ac728e35..916a2fb48450 100644
--- a/drivers/mmc/host/renesas_sdhi_core.c
+++ b/drivers/mmc/host/renesas_sdhi_core.c
@@ -361,6 +361,13 @@ static bool renesas_sdhi_check_scc_error(struct tmio_mmc_host *host)
 {
 	struct renesas_sdhi *priv = host_to_priv(host);
 
+	if (!(host->mmc->ios.timing == MMC_TIMING_UHS_SDR104) &&
+	    !(host->mmc->ios.timing == MMC_TIMING_MMC_HS200))
+		return false;
+
+	if (host->mmc->doing_retune == 1)
+		return false;
+
 	/* Check SCC error */
 	if (sd_scc_read32(host, priv, SH_MOBILE_SDHI_SCC_RVSCNTL) &
 	    SH_MOBILE_SDHI_SCC_RVSCNTL_RVSEN &&
